snippet.textDisplay:
Utterly disappointing! Maithili is the only reason this song gained some traction. Else, this is pure dhoka. This is not a song, not even fusion. It is just a rap with some folk touch. I think Maithili should do another song just to redeem herself as her presence and immense potential which could be used in a set up like coke studio was sheerly wasted. Simply trying to copy Coke studio pakistan will lead nowhere. Na ghar ka na ghaat ka raha ye genre. Coke studio brand stands for originality and art, not bandwagon. It never was, Wo bollywood music ka kam hai. This is just copycat stunt, trying to mimic the success by songs CS Pak-Season 14. This is what happens when you try too hard without having any substance in your song. Everything is overdone and Maithilis voice is also overedited. Apko Maithili jaise singer ki zarurat hi ni thi ye over-edited, un-original-idea, trying-to-copy-successful-songs, something-looking-like-a-song wali chiz banane ke liye. Kya hai yar ye, song bhi bolne layak nahi hai! Couldn't be more dissapointed. Matlab yahi sab sunna tha toh bollywood songs kaafi nahi hai kya? Coke studio ki kya zarurat thi.
Aur ye Cameo kabse hone laga song me? Jaise Pathan kis success ensure krne k liye Salman se cameo krwa diya, ye toh wahi baat h. This clearly shows ki song pe toh mehnat ki ni, baki formula laga k hit banane ki koshish ki ja rahi hai. Ravi Kishan kar kya rahe hain yahan, unka song se kya lena dena, kya logic tha iss cameo ka? Is he a singer? Does he represent Braj jiske upar ye gana h? Or holi?.. cameo ki kisko zarurat thi. Ye movie ban ri h ye song ban raha hai. Aaplog jingles banaiye commercial ads ke liye. Coke studio aapke liye nahi hai.
